: AFS 21401", "subject": ["sound recording", "interviews", "north carolina", "field recordings", "folklore"], "timestamp": "2022-04-23T09:21:35.596Z", "title": "Interview with Roy F. Woody, Jeanne Woody, and family, Laurel Springs, Ashe County, North Carolina, part 4", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc1982009_afs21401/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112201/0394.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02:data:sn92073203:00332893087:1945112201:0389/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112201/0394.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92073203/1945-11-22/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112201/0394.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02:data:sn92073203:00332893087:1945112201:0389/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112201/0394.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92073203/1945-11-22/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112201/0394.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92073203/1945-11-22/ed-1/?sp=6"], "batch": ["ncu_lagarde_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/north carolina/", "2/united states/north carolina/ashe/", "3/united states/north carolina/ashe/west jefferson/"], "contributor": ["university of north carolina at chapel hill library, chapel hill, nc"], "date": "1945-11-22", "dates": ["1945-11-22"], "description": ["PAGE SIX Conservation Farming News Weekly Items Os Interest To Ashe Farmers By j t mclaurin The New River Soil Conserva tion District recently assisted Moody Hale of the Helton com munity establish contour guides on more than 30 acres of his farm I do not plan to crop any of my farm without following a system of stripcropping and now is the time to start Mr Hale said W L McMillan of the Scott ville community has planted more than 10000 white pines on a badly eroded field on his farm and is so well pleased with the results that he plans to plant the rest of the field in pines this win ter I did not think anything would grow on that field when I bought it but it will not be but a very few years until a good crop of timber can be cut there Mr McMillan stated Hayden Goodman of the Bea ver Creek community says he is convinced that now is the time of the year to apply lime and phosphate to pastures He says many farmers do not treat their pastures until spring and they do not get the full benefits from materials"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-12T17:38:01.599Z", "group": ["ndnp/ncu", "university-of-north-carolina-chapel-hill-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92073203/1945-11-22/ed-1/?sp=6", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02:data:sn92073203:00332893087:1945112201:0394/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=284&w=207", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02:data:sn92073203:00332893087:1945112201:0394/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=568&w=415", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batc